messageBody:
On Jun 2, 2006, at 4:01 AM, junit@yahoogroups.com wrote:

> From: "Ilja Preuss" preuss@...
> Subject: Re: Digest Number 1846
>
>
>> I'm having a devil of a time understanding the code below as Java.
>> What am I missing?
>
> The introduction of generics in Java 5, perhaps?
>
> Or what exactly do you have problems with?

Here's the stretch that I'm having trouble with:

> public interface Node<T> {
> protected void process(T value) {
>
> // class
>
> public static In<T> extends Node<T> {
> public void connectFrom(Node.Out<? super T> node);
> }
>
> public static Out<T> extends Node<T> {
> public void connectTo(Node.In<? extends T> node);
> }
> }

I've pasted this into IntelliJ, with 1.5, but it doesn't compile.
Moreover I can't parse it myself with what I know about generics.
Does this look syntactically legal to you?
